gomodel:SYNGO_5219  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure S1d: STED super-resolution microscopy of hippocampal primary neurons with antibody labeling of endogenous ERGIC53 (an ER-Golgi intermediate compartment marker), postsynaptic density marker Homer1 and actin (phalloidin, in confocal mode) showed ERGIC53 at the dendritic shaft and at postsynapses in close proximity to Homer1.\n\nAuthors discussed the interpretation of ERGIC53 (one of the POI, proteins of interest);\n\"Nevertheless, in our experimental setup all POIs could be identified unambiguously in the dendritic shafts and at post-synaptic compartments. According to previous studies, the ERGIC was proposed to be rarely present in dendritic spines (PMID:28875935). However, it should be noted that in electron microscopy the ERGIC resembles endosomes, which are often found in spines, and therefore this similarity might lead to misinterpretation of the images (PMID:28559323). Furthermore, fine ERGIC53 puncta could be easily overseen or mislocalised when using diffraction-limited light microscopy. \". Experimental description: M&M: \"Cultures of dissociated rat hippocampal primary neurons were prepared from postnatal P0-P2 Wistar rats ...\"\n\nantibody:\nERGIC-53/p58 (Sigma E1031, 1:200 dilution)\n\nantibody validation is shown in Figure S11." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-04" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5219" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

